Though, I'm happy

279
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,200
that Moo

280
00:18:18,310 --> 00:18:19,990
has found someone
so completely in love with him.

281
00:18:27,130 --> 00:18:28,440
Let's toast to Moo.

282
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:29,280
Cheers.

283
00:18:29,780 --> 00:18:30,200
Alright.

284
00:18:31,740 --> 00:18:32,600
Cheers.

285
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:11,710
Tian...

286
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:19,300
What's wrong?

287
00:19:28,050 --> 00:19:28,610
I...

288
00:19:31,010 --> 00:19:32,310
I'm not seeing him anymore.

289
00:19:38,230 --> 00:19:39,290
Who?!

290
00:20:14,590 --> 00:20:15,610
From now on,

291
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:19,300
I won't get to lie on your shoulder

292
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:22,310
like this again, will I?

293
00:20:35,010 --> 00:20:36,310
I'm sorry.

294
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:42,490
Why are you sorry?

295
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:52,800
I don't want you to get in trouble

296
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,080
because of my career path.

297
00:20:58,210 --> 00:21:00,120
And that path

298
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:04,900
really can't have me in it?

299
00:21:11,570 --> 00:21:13,500
The reason I'm letting you go

300
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:18,000
is that I love you.

301
00:21:27,340 --> 00:21:28,610
One day,

302
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,300
if I ever get another chance to love you,

303
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:41,000
I'll take it without hesitation.

304
00:21:53,610 --> 00:21:54,900
I'm not going to promise

305
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:57,600
that I'll wait for you.

306
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:23,600
Could it be that someone like me

307
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:26,200
doesn't deserve to be loved?

308
00:22:26,540 --> 00:22:27,300
Is that it?

309
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:35,100
Not at all.

310
00:23:07,370 --> 00:23:08,790
Or maybe...

311
00:23:14,820 --> 00:23:17,000
You...crazy! Tian!

312
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:19,900
I'm gonna throw up!

313
00:23:26,330 --> 00:23:27,610
Have you gone absolutely nuts?

314
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:31,590
I'm happy

315
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:33,630
that you're still here with me.

316
00:23:36,770 --> 00:23:37,840
Thank you so much.

317
00:23:38,210 --> 00:23:39,210
I'm also happy.

318
00:23:43,940 --> 00:23:45,210
It's gonna be fine.

319
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:55,370
Come on,

320
00:23:58,390 --> 00:23:59,300
at least

321
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:00,890
you've got...

322
00:24:01,300 --> 00:24:01,990
me

323
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:03,310
and Moo

324
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:04,610
as your friends.

325
00:24:06,090 --> 00:24:06,990
Don't worry about being lonely.

326
00:24:09,310 --> 00:24:10,410
I'm really happy

327
00:24:11,110 --> 00:24:12,800
to have you as my friends.

328
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:18,290
Me too.

329
00:24:49,620 --> 00:24:50,620
Behind the backdrop.

330
00:24:50,930 --> 00:24:52,410
- Right?
- That was suspicious.

331
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:54,510
Look. Is it right here?

332
00:24:58,120 --> 00:24:58,970
Excuse me.

333
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:02,390
You were secretly taking photos,
weren't you?

334
00:25:04,380 --> 00:25:06,080
Did you catch any faces or names?

335
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:07,590
- Ridiculous!
- Not at all.

336
00:25:07,790 --> 00:25:10,360
I'm concerned about a privacy violation.

337
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:11,180
Oh, right.

338
00:25:11,330 --> 00:25:12,970
- There's nothing of the sort, no!
- None.

339
00:25:13,010 --> 00:25:16,150
It's a beautiful wedding,
so I wanted to take some reference photos.

340
00:25:16,540 --> 00:25:17,810
Mm...

341
00:25:17,990 --> 00:25:18,810
- Right.
- Yes.

342
00:25:20,510 --> 00:25:21,390
Hello,

343
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:22,300
Mr. Henry

344
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:23,470
and Ms. Lucy.

345
00:25:25,110 --> 00:25:26,180
My name is Jirat Dong,

346
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:28,380
but you can call me Fu.

347
00:25:28,740 --> 00:25:30,050
I'm the owner of this hotel.

348
00:25:30,170 --> 00:25:31,240
Oh...

349
00:25:32,110 --> 00:25:33,830
So you're Fu?

350
00:25:34,050 --> 00:25:36,000
Hello there!

351
00:25:36,030 --> 00:25:37,080
Hello.

352
00:25:37,110 --> 00:25:38,690
- Hello, hello.
- Right.

353
00:25:39,150 --> 00:25:42,710
I'm totally in love
with this aesthetic.

354
00:25:43,170 --> 00:25:45,710
May I ask if the hotel organized it?

355
00:25:46,280 --> 00:25:47,090
No, it's not.

356
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:50,970
It was organized by the client's team.
We just provided the space for rent.

357
00:25:51,470 --> 00:25:54,000
- Oh...
- Oh...

358
00:25:54,230 --> 00:25:56,210
I see.

359
00:26:06,610 --> 00:26:07,410
Here you go, sir.

360
00:26:12,260 --> 00:26:13,280
How much did you put in
for the wedding gift?

361
00:26:14,030 --> 00:26:15,180
Why is there only one?

362
00:26:16,210 --> 00:26:17,210
Jeez, Deputy.

363
00:26:18,010 --> 00:26:19,810
I didn't even give any money.

364
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:21,740
I just grabbed one.

365
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:24,700
We have to be more cautious.

366
00:26:25,670 --> 00:26:27,400
Sneaking out evidence like this

367
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:29,780
can make them suspicious

368
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,000
and tip them off.

369
00:26:31,490 --> 00:26:32,410
Please trust us.

370
00:26:33,700 --> 00:26:34,390
I assure you

371
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:37,800
our plan will succeed.

372
00:26:40,580 --> 00:26:42,200
I really can trust Henry

373
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:44,090
and Lucy,

374
00:26:44,550 --> 00:26:45,600
can't I?

375
00:26:49,010 --> 00:26:51,790
Have you also watched '50 First Dates'?

376
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:53,730
Wow...

377
00:26:54,730 --> 00:26:56,400
Please don't worry, Deputy.

378
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:59,690
We've made a secret deal with the hotel.

379
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:02,610
Our plan's gonna
succeed no matter what.

380
00:27:06,790 --> 00:27:09,790
Hello, allow me
to formally introduce myself.

381
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:10,700
My name is Mae,

382
00:27:10,740 --> 00:27:12,430
and he is Maze.

383
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:13,700
We are...

384
00:27:16,930 --> 00:27:18,510
police detectives.

385
00:27:19,870 --> 00:27:21,110
We're working on

386
00:27:21,400 --> 00:27:23,910
a transnational drug trafficking case.

387
00:27:24,230 --> 00:27:27,190
We kindly ask that you cooperate, Mr. Fu.

388
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:28,500
Jang...

389
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:31,210
Are they real cops?

390
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:32,240
We are.

391
00:27:32,270 --> 00:27:34,510
- You are. Okay...
- This is not a scam.

392
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:37,700
So you're saying...

393
00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:39,210
my hotel

394
00:27:39,430 --> 00:27:42,110
is being used by the mafia
to transport drugs?

395
00:27:42,280 --> 00:27:43,840
How could that even be possible?

396
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:45,100
Well, it is now.

397
00:27:45,610 --> 00:27:47,140
But you can relax.

398
00:27:47,170 --> 00:27:50,120
We'll carry it out as quietly as possible

399
00:27:50,500 --> 00:27:52,640
since this one has powerful backers.

400
00:27:53,780 --> 00:27:55,320
That's how it's supposed to be.

401
00:27:55,780 --> 00:27:56,380
I...

402
00:27:56,590 --> 00:27:58,620
couldn't risk my hotel's reputation

403
00:27:58,890 --> 00:28:00,210
be implicated in such things.

404
00:28:01,160 --> 00:28:04,110
That's right, and the press
can't know anything about it.

405
00:28:04,710 --> 00:28:05,580
Good.

406
00:28:05,790 --> 00:28:07,510
That means that you, you, you,

407
00:28:07,550 --> 00:28:08,390
and the two of us

408
00:28:08,670 --> 00:28:09,990
are all on the same page.

409
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:13,840
We'll be sure to move very quietly.

410
00:28:14,220 --> 00:28:17,960
We won't damage the hotel's reputation
in the slightest.

411
00:28:18,130 --> 00:28:20,320
I ask that this remain a secret

412
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:22,010
among everyone in this room.

413
00:28:23,130 --> 00:28:25,820
Regardless, please clear the coast for us.

414
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:26,910
Let's roll.

415
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:28,640
Roll where?
Oh...

416
00:28:29,940 --> 00:28:31,410
- To...clear the way...
- The door is right there.

417
00:28:33,460 --> 00:28:35,100
With a ceremony this big,

418
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:38,000
could it really be kept a secret?

419
00:28:38,060 --> 00:28:39,390
We will do our best.

420
00:28:40,010 --> 00:28:40,620
We will.

421
00:28:40,790 --> 00:28:42,520
You can bet Maze's life on it.

422
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:43,210
Hey!

423
00:28:47,410 --> 00:28:48,290
What was that about?

424
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:49,400
Why me?

425
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:09,300
Whoa, watch out!

426
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:19,370
Are you okay?

427
00:29:20,030 --> 00:29:21,030
Are you okay?

428
00:29:21,790 --> 00:29:22,720
I'm okay.

429
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:25,090
Oh...

430
00:29:26,700 --> 00:29:28,920
You work here, too?

431
00:29:29,900 --> 00:29:30,800
Oh, yes.

432
00:29:32,100 --> 00:29:32,810
I'll...

433
00:29:33,250 --> 00:29:34,870
The floor is wet.
Let me wipe it for you first.

434
00:29:38,330 --> 00:29:39,700
Just how many jobs do you do, anyway?

435
00:29:44,810 --> 00:29:45,990
Well...

436
00:29:50,500 --> 00:29:51,500
Thank you

437
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:53,880
for getting hurt for me.

438
00:29:57,360 --> 00:29:58,210
It's okay.

439
00:29:59,360 --> 00:30:00,280
It's my job anyway.

440
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:04,890
You still haven't told me

441
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:07,190
how many jobs you have.

442
00:30:08,310 --> 00:30:09,810
How much do you want to know?

443
00:30:16,010 --> 00:30:17,200
Fine, I don't wanna know.

444
00:30:17,690 --> 00:30:18,410
I'm heading home.

445
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:23,000
How are you gonna get home?

446
00:30:23,690 --> 00:30:24,600
I'm calling a ride.

447
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:27,720
(Tai's home)

448
00:30:40,700 --> 00:30:41,060
Hey!

449
00:30:42,690 --> 00:30:43,410
Is this you?

450
00:30:43,490 --> 00:30:46,330
(Your rider, Yu, is ready to pick you up)

451
00:30:46,390 --> 00:30:46,790
Yes.

452
00:30:50,280 --> 00:30:51,030
Then...

453
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:53,010
I'm going to clock out real quick.

454
00:30:53,310 --> 00:30:54,310
Just wait a moment,

455
00:30:54,900 --> 00:30:55,990
and I'll take you to my car.

456
00:31:59,220 --> 00:32:00,300
Who are you?

457
00:32:03,020 --> 00:32:04,310
We met at the nightclub last night.

458
00:32:04,970 --> 00:32:05,700
Don't you remember?

459
00:32:20,190 --> 00:32:22,110
So why didn't you take me home?

460
00:32:24,960 --> 00:32:26,300
Well, I don't know where you live.

461
00:32:28,060 --> 00:32:29,800
What?

462
00:32:31,460 --> 00:32:33,200
So why didn't you...

463
00:32:34,990 --> 00:32:36,910
take me back to your place?

464
00:32:37,420 --> 00:32:38,010
No way.

465
00:32:39,250 --> 00:32:40,190
You wanted to hook up

466
00:32:40,770 --> 00:32:41,610
the first time we met?

467
00:32:43,310 --> 00:32:43,900
Well...

468
00:32:45,970 --> 00:32:46,760
Sounds pretty normal to me.

469
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:48,740
I'm not that into you.

470
00:32:52,740 --> 00:32:53,740
Kids,

471
00:32:53,940 --> 00:32:55,490
I'm about to close.

472
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:56,390
Go home already.

473
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:59,520
One of you slept like the dead,

474
00:33:00,360 --> 00:33:02,920
while the other stayed up
watching over him all night.

475
00:33:03,200 --> 00:33:04,410
How adorable!

476
00:33:05,700 --> 00:33:06,700
Come on,

477
00:33:07,020 --> 00:33:07,770
- let's go home.
- How cute is that.

478
00:33:08,470 --> 00:33:09,450
Your home, right?

479
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:10,480
I'm going back to my place.

480
00:33:10,520 --> 00:33:11,430
You head back to yours.

481
00:33:11,460 --> 00:33:12,500
Can't I come with you?

482
00:33:12,580 --> 00:33:13,410
I'm going back to mine,

483
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:14,490
so go back to yours.

484
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,380
A morning kiss.

485
00:34:00,220 --> 00:34:01,600
Still sleepy, huh?

486
00:34:02,820 --> 00:34:04,370
I didn't sleep last night.

487
00:34:08,220 --> 00:34:09,220
So...

488
00:34:09,450 --> 00:34:10,400
How about this?

489
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:13,480
You don't have to intern today.

490
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:16,030
How can I do that,

491
00:34:16,590 --> 00:34:16,960
hmm?

492
00:34:17,980 --> 00:34:19,780
I'll have Jang sort it out for you.

493
00:34:20,490 --> 00:34:21,330
You can't do that.

494
00:34:21,810 --> 00:34:23,310
How will others think of me, then?

495
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:25,170
I'll go to work anyway.

496
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:27,590
I'm thinking that...

497
00:34:29,310 --> 00:34:30,800
I won't let you intern anymore

498
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:32,600
because I

499
00:34:32,910 --> 00:34:34,470
have a new position for you.

500
00:34:35,580 --> 00:34:36,700
What position are you talking about?

501
00:34:37,270 --> 00:34:38,800
I'm not your a full-time employee.

502
00:34:39,300 --> 00:34:40,090
The position of...

503
00:34:41,340 --> 00:34:43,500
a lovely hubby of mine.

504
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:46,900
Fu!

505
00:34:47,360 --> 00:34:48,810
You like it, huh?!

506
00:34:49,070 --> 00:34:50,190
This position

507
00:34:50,890 --> 00:34:52,570
is more important than full-time employee

508
00:34:53,730 --> 00:34:56,040
because once you're appointed,
you have to do it forever.

509
00:34:58,740 --> 00:34:59,990
I'd better take a shower.

510
00:35:00,330 --> 00:35:00,980
Hey!

511
00:35:01,340 --> 00:35:01,910
Where are you going?

512
00:35:02,390 --> 00:35:03,330
I'm going to take a shower.

513
00:35:04,100 --> 00:35:04,890
- Five...
- It's already late.

514
00:35:05,170 --> 00:35:05,890
Give me five minutes.

515
00:35:06,550 --> 00:35:07,210
No, I won't

516
00:35:09,660 --> 00:35:11,190
I'm not going to give you that.

517
00:35:13,210 --> 00:35:14,600
Hurry up. Do your job.

518
00:35:14,990 --> 00:35:15,610
No.
Why should I do that?

519
00:35:16,640 --> 00:35:17,600
It's your new position.

520
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:19,400
I haven't accepted that yet.

521
00:35:20,860 --> 00:35:21,710
What about last night?

522
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:22,420
Hmm?

523
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:24,290
Were you already my hubby then?

524
00:35:24,600 --> 00:35:26,210
Who was that? I completely forgot.

525
00:35:26,250 --> 00:35:27,710
- You forgot?
- Yeah.

526
00:35:30,830 --> 00:35:32,580
I'll jog your memory.

527
00:35:57,590 --> 00:35:59,100
I'd like to apologize to you

528
00:35:59,230 --> 00:36:02,620
for not welcoming you personally.

529
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:06,210
Finally, we get to meet.

530
00:36:06,810 --> 00:36:08,310
Is everything alright?

531
00:36:09,810 --> 00:36:11,100
Yes, it is.

532
00:36:11,300 --> 00:36:13,890
But the guest and seat numbers
aren't finalized yet.

533
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:16,200
Lang had me set aside some seats

534
00:36:16,620 --> 00:36:17,990
for special guests.

535
00:36:19,970 --> 00:36:22,510
It would be great if...

536
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:26,810
I was one of the honored guests
at your wedding

537
00:36:27,210 --> 00:36:28,500
with Mr. Lang.

538
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:30,710
It would be our honor, too.

539
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:33,090
Since you said it yourself like this,

540
00:36:33,650 --> 00:36:36,110
how could I not invite you?

541
00:36:37,030 --> 00:36:38,200
In Bangkok,

542
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:40,180
you seem to have
a wide network of contacts.

543
00:36:40,900 --> 00:36:42,910
You probably have many partners.

544
00:36:44,110 --> 00:36:46,490
The business market in Bangkok
is really big, Ms. Lin.

545
00:36:47,310 --> 00:36:48,410
My partners and I

546
00:36:49,190 --> 00:36:52,010
are always ready to share it with you.

547
00:36:53,340 --> 00:36:54,710
So, I hope that...

548
00:36:55,830 --> 00:36:57,110
the money you put in the box

549
00:36:57,310 --> 00:36:59,770
will be enough to keep us connected.

550
00:37:01,500 --> 00:37:02,210
Ryan.

551
00:37:15,690 --> 00:37:17,710
Young adults are really hot-headed,
aren't they?

552
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:25,600
Whoa.

553
00:37:26,430 --> 00:37:27,490
You're not with Fu, huh?

554
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,090
He told me

555
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:33,410
I don't have to intern anymore.

556
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:35,000
That's strange.

557
00:37:35,890 --> 00:37:36,480
How come?

558
00:37:37,350 --> 00:37:40,200
Maybe the honeymoon phase is over,

559
00:37:40,410 --> 00:37:40,890
like...

560
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:42,720
he's bored of you or something?

561
00:37:42,850 --> 00:37:44,080
- There you go.
- What?

562
00:37:44,180 --> 00:37:45,390
If my brother hears that,

563
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:46,440
you're dead meat.

564
00:37:46,470 --> 00:37:48,620
What? That's possible.

565
00:37:48,810 --> 00:37:49,900
Before being together,

566
00:37:50,030 --> 00:37:51,510
he was literally obsessed with Moo.

